        How does Web Everything compare to the feature sets of React, Angular, Vue, Svelte, Lit, Solid, and Qwik?
        The table below maps 74 features across 14 categories to their Web Everything equivalents, identifying where adapters are needed and where features are missing.
    </p>

    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; font-size: 0.85rem;">
            <div style="width: 18px; height: 18px; border-radius: 3px; border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.15); background: #d4edda;"></div> Covered
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; font-size: 0.85rem;">
            <div style="width: 18px; height: 18px; border-radius: 3px; border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.15); background: #d1ecf1;"></div> Concept / spec only
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; font-size: 0.85rem;">
            <div style="width: 18px; height: 18px; border-radius: 3px; border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.15); background: #fff3cd;"></div> Missing Adapter
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; font-size: 0.85rem;">
            <div style="width: 18px; height: 18px; border-radius: 3px; border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.15); background: #f8d7da;"></div> Missing Feature
