    <h4 id="strongest-areas">Strongest Areas (at or above parity)</h4>
    <ul style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
        <li><strong>Routing</strong> (8/10): Navigation API, URLPattern, guards, loaders, prefetch, transitions, scroll restoration, lazy loading</li>
        <li><strong>Component Model</strong> (5/6): Class components, lifecycle, props, refs, web component interop, traits</li>
        <li><strong>Dependency Injection</strong> (3/4): Hierarchical DI, singletons, scoped providers</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility</strong> (3/4): ARIA roles built into blocks, keyboard navigation, live regions</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 id="missing-adapters">Missing Adapters (7 &mdash; bridgeable with transforms)</h4>
    <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        These features exist conceptually in Web Everything but need a syntax bridge or thin adapter layer:
    </p>
    <table style="font-size: 0.85rem;">
