        </div>
        <div style="padding: 1rem; background: #fff5f5; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #feb2b2;">
            <h4 style="margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: #c53030;" class="no-toc">i18n (2)</h4>
            <ul style="font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0; padding-left: 1.25rem; color: #742a2a;">
                <li>Localization</li>
                <li>RTL support</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div style="padding: 1rem; background: #fff5f5; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #feb2b2;">
            <h4 style="margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: #c53030;" class="no-toc">Animations (2)</h4>
            <ul style="font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0; padding-left: 1.25rem; color: #742a2a;">
                <li>Layout animations</li>
                <li>Spring-based physics</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h4 id="unique-to-we">Unique to Web Everything</h4>
    <ul style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
        <li><strong>Invoker Commands API</strong> &mdash; <code>commandfor</code>/<code>command</code> throughout (no other framework has this)</li>
        <li><strong>Intent Protocol</strong> &mdash; abstract UX contracts that decouple WHAT from HOW</li>
        <li><strong>Provider-scoped typed events</strong> &mdash; <code>listenForScoped</code> discrimination via injector chain</li>
        <li><strong>Comment-based virtual elements</strong> &mdash; preserves CSS Grid/Flex parent-child relationships</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="comparison-block" style="background: rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.05); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary); margin: 1.5rem 0;">
